If you want to know how `QSqlQueryModel` works, you should look at the [source code][1]. The class handles (should handle) the partial fetching out of box, and you don&#39;t need to implement your own mechanism.&lt;br&gt;
Basically if the view needs to show more items due to scrolling it down, model fetches another set (255 according to implementation) rows and appends them to the bottom.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Basically all models are aimed to provide performance efficient fetching. The main idea is that the view requests more data from its model as soon as it needs to show it. If you have 1000 data items and the view is not able to show them at once, it doesn&#39;t need all 1000. If you debug your model you will see how the `QAbstractItemModel::data()` function called and with which arguments: only visible model indexes provided.

  [1]: https://code.woboq.org/qt5/qtbase/src/sql/models/qsqlquerymodel.cpp.html#_ZN21QSqlQueryModelPrivate8prefetchEi

